<item>
            <title>[CXF-6976] High memory footprint when maven assembly plugin is used together with cxf-codegen-plugin</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6976</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When assembly plugin is used together with cxf codegen plugin, it is using up massive amount of memory, leading to frequent OOM errors and long build times. When used alone, both plugins behave nicely.&lt;br/&gt;
Attached POM can be used to replicate the issue. When CXF plugin is commented out, assembly plugin finishes within a few seconds, using up minimal amount of memory. When the POM is executed as provided, Maven throws OOM when given 2GB of memory.&lt;br/&gt;
See also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MASSEMBLY-825&quot; title=&quot;High memory footprint when jar-with-dependencies is used together with cxf-codegen-plugin&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MASSEMBLY-825&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MASSEMBLY-825&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for related assembly-plugin report.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Apache Maven 3.3.9 (bb52d8502b132ec0a5a3f4c09453c07478323dc5; 2015-11-10T17:41:47+01:00)&lt;br/&gt;
Maven home: C:\projects\build\apache-maven-3.3.9\bin\..&lt;br/&gt;
Java version: 1.8.0_102, vendor: Oracle Corporation&lt;br/&gt;
Java home: C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_102\jre&lt;br/&gt;
