&lt;p&gt;Note: there is a workaround if you add &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;-Dorg.apache.cxf.JDKBugHacks.defaultUsesCaches=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to your MAVEN_OPTS variable, then it should work .  That cache needs to be disabled during runtime, but not for tooling so the maven plugin (and command line tools) will now set that flag.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
